text: Lysiphragma howesii is a species of moth in the family Tineidae. It was described by Ambrose Quail in 1901. This species is endemic to New Zealand. ==References== ==External links== *Image of type specimen of Lysiphragma howesii *Citizen science images of moth Category:Moths described in 1901 Category:Tineidae Category:Moths of New Zealand Category:Endemic fauna of New Zealand
